# Base de Datos — Schema Exacto Áurea Flow

## REGLA DE ORO
Antes de hacer cualquier query o insert, consulta este archivo.
Las columnas aquí listadas son las que EXISTEN en la BD real.
No inventes columnas. No asumas nombres.

## Tablas y columnas verificadas

### profiles
id, full_name, role, phone, avatar_url, is_active, created_at, updated_at
role CHECK IN ('admin', 'empleado', 'cliente')

### products
id, category_id, sku, name, description, unit, base_price, cost_price,
min_stock, is_active, image_url, created_at, updated_at
CAMPO: name (NO nombre)

### customers
id, business_name, contact_name, email, phone, address, notes, 
is_active, created_at, updated_at
CRÍTICO: email debe coincidir EXACTAMENTE (case-sensitive) con auth.users.email

### raw_materials
id, name, unit, current_stock, min_stock, unit_cost, supplier, 
is_active, created_at, updated_at

### production_orders
id, order_number, product_id, planned_quantity, actual_quantity,
waste_quantity, waste_notes, waste_photo_url, production_date, lot_id,
status CHECK IN ('pendiente','en_proceso','completada','cancelada'),
notes, created_by, assigned_to, completed_at, created_at, updated_at
FK ambigua — SIEMPRE usar: profiles!production_orders_assigned_to_fkey(full_name)

### production_raw_material_usage
id, production_order_id, raw_material_id, planned_quantity, actual_quantity, created_at
CAMPO: planned_quantity (NO quantity_used)

### inventory_lots
id, product_id, lot_number, production_date, expiry_date,
initial_quantity, current_quantity, committed_quantity, 
unit_cost, notes, created_at, updated_at
SIN columnas: production_order_id, is_active (no existen)

### inventory_movements
id, lot_id, product_id,
movement_type CHECK IN ('entrada','salida','ajuste','merma'),
quantity, unit_cost, reference_id, reference_type, notes, created_by, created_at
movement_type entrada al completar producción
movement_type salida al entregar pedido

### orders
id, order_number, customer_id,
status CHECK IN ('borrador','confirmado','en_preparacion','listo','entregado','cancelado'),
payment_status CHECK IN ('pendiente','parcial','pagado'),
total, paid_amount, delivery_date, delivery_address, notes,
confirmed_by_customer, confirmed_by_employee, created_by, created_at, updated_at

### order_items
id, order_id, product_id, lot_id, quantity, unit_price, discount_pct, subtotal, created_at

### payments
id, order_id, amount, payment_method, reference, notes, created_by, created_at

### customer_prices
id, customer_id, product_id, fixed_price, discount_pct, notes, is_active, created_at, updated_at

### purchases
id, raw_material_id, supplier, quantity, unit_cost, total,
paid_amount, payment_status CHECK IN ('pendiente', 'parcial', 'pagado', 'cancelado'),
purchase_date, invoice_number, notes,
received_quantity, reception_notes,
reception_status CHECK IN ('pendiente', 'recibido_completo', 'recibido_parcial', 'cancelado'),
created_by, created_at, updated_at

### purchase_payments
id, purchase_id, amount,
payment_method CHECK IN ('efectivo', 'transferencia', 'cheque', 'tarjeta'),
reference, notes, created_by, created_at

## Lógicas críticas de negocio — NUNCA violar

### FIFO sagrado
Al confirmar pedido: query inventory_lots ORDER BY production_date ASC
con current_quantity > committed_quantity suficiente.
El PRIMER resultado es siempre el lote más antiguo.

### Merma en producción
cantidad_neta = actual_quantity - waste_quantity
inventory_lots.current_quantity = cantidad_neta (NO actual_quantity)
inventory_movements.quantity = cantidad_neta

### Doble confirmación de entrega
status = 'entregado' SOLO cuando:
confirmed_by_customer = true AND confirmed_by_employee = true
Al confirmar: descontar current_quantity, limpiar committed_quantity,
registrar movimientos tipo 'salida'

### Cancelar pedido
SIEMPRE liberar committed_quantity de todos los lotes asignados

### Deuda de compras
SOLO payment_status IN ('pendiente', 'parcial')
NUNCA filtrar con != 'pagado' — eso incluiría canceladas (BUG)

### Precios por cliente (prioridad estricta)
1. customer_prices.fixed_price (si existe y is_active = true)
2. base_price * (1 - discount_pct/100) (si existe descuento)
3. products.base_price (precio estándar)
